comments: "Down Where the Watermelon Grows" was written for Eddie Foy for his May 24, 1909 performance in the "Lambs Star Gambol" at the Metropolitan Opera House in New York City. The Lambs Club was a professional theatrical club based in New York City. Starting in 1888 the club produced shows called "gambols" which raised money for charity.
